    "History": {
      "rows": [
        [
          "Staff Generated History",
          "",
          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "You live up to everyone's stereotype of a Toreador - foppish, shallow, indulgent. You only wear the best fashions and attend the most culturally refined events. You know how to play this game, and you do it very well. What no one has yet figured out, however, is that you hate being a vampire. You were Embraced against your will, and utterly loathe your sire for what they made you. All this game-playing is to one purpose, and one purpose only: kill your sire, then kill the Prince who gave them permission to Embrace you. As the result of your endeavors, you have become a rather spectacular spy, as well as a talented politician."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "",
          "Embrace Date:",
          "",
          "Embrace Location:"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Who You Know",
          "Your relationship to these people is described. This may mean they do not know you."
        ],
        [
          "1: Franky the Tail: You've done business with him before. He's disgusting, of course - all Nosferatu are. But he's a solid dealer."
        ],
        [
          "2: Oliver/Olive Johnson: You get the feeling that M. Johnson has seen some shit. They may be a useful teacher for combat skills."
        ],
        [
          "3: Theodor/Teresa van Holder: You appreciate M. van Holder's talent and wonder if they can teach you more about how to work the system to get what you want."
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Starting Goals",
          "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        ],
        [
          "1: Killing a vampire is a big deal. You'll need to accrue enough boons that you can eventually petition for Right of Destruction (and get it)."
        ],
        [
          "2: In order to get boons, you'll need to trade something of equal value. In vampire society, that means information. Collect as many secrets as you can, and find buyers for them."
        ],
        [
          "3: Of course, once you get Right of Destruction, you'll still need to get the job done. Find people who will teach you how to fight (though maybe don't tell them precisely why you want to learn)."
        ],
        [],
